le)\n    ↓\n... (repeat)\n    ↓\nFully Connected Layer (classification/generation)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This pattern (conv → pooling) is repeated one or more times in CNNs."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental Model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of pooling as "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"zooming out"},{"type":"text","text":" on a map:\n- You're looking at a detailed city map (feature map from convolution)\n- When you zoom out, individual streets disappear, but major highways remain visible\n- You still know where the city is, even if you can't see every street\n- The map is smaller but contains the essential information"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Or think of it as "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"summarizing a report"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- A 10-page report contains detailed information\n- You create a 1-page executive summary\n- The summary captures key points but omits minor details\n- Readers can quickly understand the main message"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pooling "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"downsamples spatial dimensions"},{"type":"text","text":" of feature maps, reducing computation while retaining important information"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Max pooling"},{"type":"text","text":" (most common) preserves strongest features; "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"average pooling"},{"type":"text","text":" smooths representations"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Standard configuration: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2×2 pool size with stride 2"},{"type":"text","text":" reduces feature map to 1/4 size"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pooling introduces "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"translation invariance"},{"type":"text","text":", critical for recognizing objects at different positions"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Enables "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"deeper networks"},{"type":"text","text":" and improves "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"generalization"},{"type":"text","text":" by reducing overfitting"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In generative AI, pooling helps CNNs (like GANs) efficiently process images while maintaining spatial hierarchy"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pooling remains a standard component in CNN architectures for vision-based generative models, though some modern architectures (e.g., Vision Transformers) use alternative downsampling strategies."}]}]}}
